SIMPLE: pronunciation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pronunciation
<hw>Pro*nun`ci*a"tion</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>pronunciation</ets>, L. <ets>pronunciatio</ets>. See
<er>Pronounce</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of uttering with articulation; the act of
giving the proper sound and accent; utterance; <as>as, the
<ex>pronunciation</ex> of syllables of words; distinct or indistinct
<ex>pronunciation</ex>.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The mode of uttering words or sentences.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Rhet.)</fld> <def>The art of manner of uttering a
discourse publicly with propriety and gracefulness; -- now called
<altname>delivery</altname>.</def> <rj><au>J. Q. Adams.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pronunciative</ent>⟦br⟧
